article.headline: Brown 61, Princeton 43
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Matt Mullery had 19 points and six assists as Brown snapped a seven-game losing streak with a 61-43 win over Princeton on Saturday. Peter Sullivan added 13 points and Adrian Williams finished with 11 for the Bears (7-15, 1-7 Ivy League), who limited Princeton to their lowest offensive output this season. Mullery connected on 8 of 10 from the field to help the Bears earn their first conference win. The teams were tied at 21-21 at halftime, but Brown ran off a 17-3 run to open the second half. Princeton (9-10, 4-2) led by five points with 10:04 left in the opening half. The Tigers were led by Kareem Maddox, who scored 10 points. Princeton's previous low was against Rutgers on Dec. 10 when they scored 44.
